---
import AdminLayout from '../../layouts/admin/admin-layout.astro'
import PageHeader from '../../components/common/page-header.astro'
import Toc from '../../components/toc/toc.astro'
import { getPathPrefix } from '../../../utils/path.js'

const pageHeaderProps = {
  title: 'FAQs',
  breadcrumbs: [
    { label: 'Docs', href: getPathPrefix('/docs') },
    { label: 'FAQs', class: 'active' }
  ]
}
---

<AdminLayout
  currentPath="docs/faq"
  title="Frequently Asked Questions"
  description="Find answers to common questions about the HOA template package, including setup, features, customization, and support."
>
  <PageHeader {...pageHeaderProps} />

  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-9 order-1 order-lg-0">
      <h2 class="h3 mb-2" id="general">General Questions</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Common questions about purchasing and using the HOA template package.</p>
      <div class="mb-5">
        <div class="accordion" id="generalAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="general1">
              <button
                class="accordion-button"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#generalAnswer1"
                aria-expanded="true"
                aria-controls="generalAnswer1"
              >
                What exactly do I get when I purchase this HOA template?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="generalAnswer1"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse show"
              aria-labelledby="general1"
              data-bs-parent="#generalAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>When you purchase our HOA template package, you receive:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>3 Complete Themes:</strong> Classic, Modern, and Premium designs</li>
                  <li><strong>25+ HTML Pages:</strong> All essential pages for HOA websites</li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Admin Dashboard:</strong> Complete backend interface with user management
                  </li>
                  <li><strong>Source Files:</strong> HTML, CSS/SCSS, JavaScript, and all assets</li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Documentation:</strong> Comprehensive setup and customization guide
                  </li>
                  <li><strong>Free Updates:</strong> Future improvements and new features</li>
                  <li><strong>Support:</strong> 6 months of email support included</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="general2">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#generalAnswer2"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="generalAnswer2"
              >
                Is this template suitable for my HOA size?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="generalAnswer2"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="general2"
              data-bs-parent="#generalAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>Yes! Our template is designed to scale with communities of all sizes:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Small Communities (10-50 homes):</strong> Perfect for basic communication
                    and announcements
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Medium Communities (50-200 homes):</strong> Ideal for amenity management
                    and resident portals
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Large Communities (200+ homes):</strong> Handles complex user management
                    and extensive features
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                  The admin panel includes user management tools that can handle hundreds of
                  residents, and the design scales beautifully regardless of your community size.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="general3">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#generalAnswer3"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="generalAnswer3"
              >
                Can I use this template for multiple HOA communities?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="generalAnswer3"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="general3"
              data-bs-parent="#generalAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>Our licensing allows you to use the template for multiple projects:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Single License:</strong> Use for one HOA community website</li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Extended License:</strong> Use for multiple communities or client projects
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Developer License:</strong> Unlimited usage for web development agencies
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                  Each license includes the same features and support - choose based on your usage
                  needs. Contact us if you need a custom licensing arrangement.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="h3 mb-2" id="technical">Technical Questions</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Technical requirements and customization information.</p>
      <div class="mb-5">
        <div class="accordion" id="technicalAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="tech1">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#techAnswer1"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="techAnswer1"
              >
                What are the technical requirements to use this template?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="techAnswer1"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="tech1"
              data-bs-parent="#technicalAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p><strong>For Development:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Node.js (version 16 or higher)</li>
                  <li>Code editor (VS Code, Sublime, etc.)</li>
                  <li>Basic knowledge of HTML/CSS</li>
                  <li>Web browser for testing</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>For Hosting:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Any modern web hosting service</li>
                  <li>Support for static files or Node.js hosting</li>
                  <li>SSL certificate (recommended)</li>
                  <li>Domain name for your HOA</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                  The template works with popular hosting services like Netlify, Vercel, AWS, and
                  traditional shared hosting.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="tech2">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#techAnswer2"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="techAnswer2"
              >
                How do I customize the colors and branding?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="techAnswer2"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="tech2"
              data-bs-parent="#technicalAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>Customizing the template is straightforward with our SCSS variable system:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Colors:</strong> Edit the variables in <code
                      >src/scss/variables/_colors.scss</code
                    >
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Fonts:</strong> Update font imports and variables in <code
                      >src/scss/variables/_typography.scss</code
                    >
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Logo:</strong> Replace logo files in <code>src/assets/img/</code> folder
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Theme:</strong> Choose from 3 pre-built themes or customize further
                  </li>
                </ol>
                <p>
                  Our documentation includes a complete customization guide with examples and best
                  practices.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="tech3">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#techAnswer3"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="techAnswer3"
              >
                Is the template mobile-responsive?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="techAnswer3"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="tech3"
              data-bs-parent="#technicalAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>Yes! The template is fully responsive and optimized for all devices:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Mobile First:</strong> Designed starting with mobile devices</li>
                  <li><strong>Bootstrap 5:</strong> Built on the latest responsive framework</li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Touch Friendly:</strong> Optimized touch targets for mobile interaction
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Fast Loading:</strong> Optimized images and assets for mobile networks
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Cross-Device Testing:</strong> Tested on phones, tablets, and desktops
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                  The admin panel is also fully responsive, allowing board members to manage the
                  community from any device.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="tech4">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#techAnswer4"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="techAnswer4"
              >
                Can I integrate this with my existing HOA management software?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="techAnswer4"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="tech4"
              data-bs-parent="#technicalAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>The template is designed to be flexible and integrate with various systems:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <strong>API Ready:</strong> Built with modern JavaScript for easy API integration
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Database Agnostic:</strong> Can work with any backend database system
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Form Integration:</strong> Easy to connect forms to your existing systems
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Third-party Services:</strong> Compatible with payment processors, email
                    services, etc.
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                  Our support team can provide guidance on specific integrations during your support
                  period.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="h3 mb-2" id="customization">Customization & Features</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Questions about setting up and extending the template functionality.</p>
      <div class="mb-5">
        <div class="accordion" id="customizationAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="custom1">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#customAnswer1"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="customAnswer1"
              >
                How do I set up the admin panel and user accounts?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="customAnswer1"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="custom1"
              data-bs-parent="#customizationAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>Setting up the admin panel involves these steps:</p>
                <ol>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Initial Setup:</strong> Follow our quick start guide to configure the admin
                    area
                  </li>
                  <li><strong>Admin Account:</strong> Create the first administrator account</li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>User Roles:</strong> Set up different permission levels (Admin, Board Member,
                    Resident)
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Resident Import:</strong> Bulk import resident data or add manually
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Customize Settings:</strong> Configure community-specific settings and preferences
                  </li>
                </ol>
                <p>
                  The documentation includes detailed screenshots and step-by-step instructions for
                  the entire setup process.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="custom2">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#customAnswer2"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="customAnswer2"
              >
                Can I add my own pages and sections?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="customAnswer2"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="custom2"
              data-bs-parent="#customizationAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>Absolutely! The template is designed for easy extension:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Component Library:</strong> Use existing components to build new pages quickly
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Page Templates:</strong> Follow established patterns for consistent design
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Navigation:</strong> Easy to add new menu items and navigation links
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Content Sections:</strong> Modular design allows mixing and matching sections
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Examples Included:</strong> Multiple page layouts to use as starting points
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                  Common additions include: Rules & Regulations pages, Community Calendar, Photo
                  Gallery, and Board Meeting Minutes.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="custom3">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#customAnswer3"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="customAnswer3"
              >
                How does the amenity booking system work?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="customAnswer3"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="custom3"
              data-bs-parent="#customizationAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>The amenity booking system includes:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Amenity Management:</strong> Add pools, tennis courts, clubhouse, etc.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Availability Calendar:</strong> Visual calendar showing available time slots
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Booking Rules:</strong> Set advance booking limits, maximum duration, etc.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Approval Process:</strong> Option for automatic or manual booking approval
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Email Notifications:</strong> Automatic confirmations and reminders
                  </li>
                  <li><strong>Resident Portal:</strong> Easy booking interface for residents</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Admins can view all bookings, manage conflicts, and generate usage reports.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="h3 mb-2" id="support">Support & Updates</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Information about support services and template updates.</p>
      <div class="mb-5">
        <div class="accordion" id="supportAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="support1">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#supportAnswer1"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="supportAnswer1"
              >
                What kind of support do you provide?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="supportAnswer1"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="support1"
              data-bs-parent="#supportAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>We provide comprehensive support for all customers:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <strong>6 Months Email Support:</strong> Direct access to our development team
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Setup Assistance:</strong> Help with initial installation and configuration
                  </li>
                  <li><strong>Customization Guidance:</strong> Advice on template modifications</li>
                  <li><strong>Bug Fixes:</strong> Quick resolution of any issues you encounter</li>
                  <li><strong>Best Practices:</strong> Recommendations for optimal usage</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                  <strong>Response Times:</strong> We typically respond within 24 hours on business days.
                  Urgent issues are prioritized.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="support2">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#supportAnswer2"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="supportAnswer2"
              >
                Do you provide free updates?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="supportAnswer2"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="support2"
              data-bs-parent="#supportAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>Yes! All customers receive free updates including:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li><strong>Security Updates:</strong> Important security patches and fixes</li>
                  <li><strong>Browser Compatibility:</strong> Updates for new browser versions</li>
                  <li><strong>Bug Fixes:</strong> Resolution of reported issues</li>
                  <li><strong>New Features:</strong> Additional components and functionality</li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Framework Updates:</strong> Updates to Bootstrap and other dependencies
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                  Updates are delivered via email with detailed changelog and upgrade instructions.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h3 class="accordion-header" id="support3">
              <button
                class="accordion-button collapsed"
                type="button"
                data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                data-bs-target="#supportAnswer3"
                aria-expanded="false"
                aria-controls="supportAnswer3"
              >
                What if I need custom development work?
              </button>
            </h3>
            <div
              id="supportAnswer3"
              class="accordion-collapse collapse"
              aria-labelledby="support3"
              data-bs-parent="#supportAccordion"
            >
              <div class="accordion-body">
                <p>We offer custom development services for additional requirements:</p>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Custom Features:</strong> Build specific functionality for your community
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Third-party Integrations:</strong> Connect with payment systems, management
                    software
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Design Customization:</strong> Major design changes beyond the included themes
                  </li>
                  <li><strong>Backend Development:</strong> Custom server-side functionality</li>
                  <li>
                    <strong>Migration Services:</strong> Help moving from your current website
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <p>Contact our team for a custom quote based on your specific requirements.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="mb-3">
          If you don't find your question listed above, you can always reach out to us with your
          queries.
        </p>
        <a href="mailto:support@asterodigital.com" class="btn btn-outline-primary">
          <i class="ri-mail-line me-2"></i>Contact Support
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <Toc />
  </div>
</AdminLayout>
